  "description": "Swedish family history expert and former chief physician, Lars Henrik August Edling was born on March 4th, 1878 in Stockholm to physician August E. and Charlotte Vult v. Steijern. He married Ester Koch in 1909 and they had three children together. Edling was educated at Uppsala University and Karolinska Institute where he earned a Bachelor of Medicine in 1901, a Medical License in 1907, and a Doctor of Medicine in 1918. He was an assistant at Karolinska Institute and Serafimerlasarettet, and acting assistant at Serafimerlasarettet. He was in charge of the radiology department at Lund University Hospital and Malmö City Hospital, and was assistant and head of the university clinical radiology institute in Lund. He was a docent of medical radiology, chief physician of the radiology institute and radiology department at the hospital in Lund, professor appointed in 1939, and chief physician at King Gustaf V's Jubilee Clinic in 1941. He wrote papers on radiodiagnostic and radiotherapy, co-edited Acta Radiologica from 1921, was a member of several international medical societies, and has been awarded several honors, including the Order of Vasa and the Nordic Forestry, Agriculture and Veterinary Medicine Medal."
